// @test regression/INV065-shadowed-scalar-member
// @description A scalar local (string param) shadowing a builtin namespace name does NOT suppress the undefined-member check: scalars carry no builtin methods, so ns.member(...) with an unknown member is TV's CE10271 "method or method reference" even when shadowed (probed p01/p06/p07, 2026-06-19). See investigations/INV065-shadow-gate-oversuppresses-member-calls/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=9, column=5, message="Could not find method or method reference 'timeframe.changex'"
// @expects error: line=11, column=5, message="Could not find method or method reference 'str.trimx'"
//@version=6
indicator("x")
// A SCALAR local (string param) shadows the builtin namespace name. Scalars
// carry no builtin methods (INV065 p06/p07), so `ns.member(...)` with an
// unknown member is still TV's CE10271 - phrased "method or method reference"
// for the value/shadow form (probed p01, 2026-06-19). The pre-INV065 shadow
// gate suppressed this, a false negative the #48 mutation harness surfaced.
f(simple string timeframe) =>
    timeframe.changex(timeframe)
g(series string str) =>
    str.trimx(str)
plot(f("D") and g("a") ? 1 : 0)
